	<http://www.cidoc-crm.org/cidoc-crm/P78_is_identified_by> "Supposedly a bishop in Illyria, Dalmatia, with his mother, Anthia. He was a Roman, educated by Bishop Dynamius. At the age of twenty, Eleutherius himself became a bishop and was arrested for converting an imperial official. \n                  He was clubbed to death and Anthia was beheaded." .
